field_edited_text.value:
Acknowledgment





THE J. E. Greiner Company would like to express appreciation—to
J. Glenn Beall, Chairman, Dr. Homer E. Tabler, Past Chairman, Frank
F. Luthardt and Elmer R. Jarboe, Members, Nathan L. Smith, Chief
Engineer, Austin F. Shure, Engineer of Surveys, William A. Codd, Chief
Auditor, L. H. Steuart, Secretary, Walter C. Hopkins, Bridge Engineer,
Clarence P. Taylor, Director, Highway Planning Survey, and the Engineer-
ing Staff of the State Roads Commission for their cooperation and assistance
in performing the preliminary work necessary for the preparation of this
report; to B. Howell Griswold, Jr., for his helpful guidance in fiscal matters
affecting the engineering work; to Herbert R. O’Conor, Attorney General,
and Thomas M. Jenifer, Special Assistant Attorney General, of Maryland,
to Robie L. Mitchell, and Messrs. Armstrong, Machen and Allen, Attorneys,
for their prompt attention to legal matters affecting the engineering work;
to William S. Gordy, State Comptroller, and his staff, to Dr. Abel Wolman,
Chairman, and each of the other members of the Bridge Supervisory Com-
mittee, and to Coverdale and Colpitts, for their cooperation; and to each
member of J. E. Greiner Company’s staff of engineers and assistants for
their untiring efforts to meet the scheduled completion dates for the different
parts of the engineering work necessary to be done in order to complete
this report.

Xix
